    <div style="font-size:18px;line-height:31px;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;color:#555555;text-align:left;"><p style="margin: 0;font-size: 18px;line-height: 31px"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 31px;"><p><strong>The Future of Cable TV?  </strong>A two-day workshop at ITU recently focused on the <a href="https://www.itu.int/en/mediacentre/Pages/2018-CM02.aspx">‘Future of Cable TV’</a> in a converged ICT marketplace.  Impacted by technological, service and regulatory changes &#8212; infrastructure and connectivity will be key features for the<a href="https://news.itu.int/future-cable-tv-look-like/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> future of digital TV services.</a> And it is essential that the technical standards, such as those developed by ITU, ensure seamless interoperability. View photos from the event <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/itupictures/sets/72157692625239985">here. </a></p>
